Mozambique is regularly affected by natural disasters, including floods, drought and cyclones.
Tropical Storm Eloise is expected to strengthen to a Tropical Cyclone, bringing hazardous sea and weather conditions to Central and Southern Mozambique from Friday 22 January 2020. It is expected to affect Sofala, Inhambane, Gaza and Maputo Provinces. There is a risk of flooding in affected areas. Monitor local reports and international weather updates from the World Meteorological Organisation, check your routes before travelling around the country and follow the advice of the local authorities.
